SB250 INTRODUCED
29
30 A BILL
31 TO BE ENTITLED
32 AN ACT
33
34 Relating to the Alabama Indian Affairs Commission; to
35 amend Sections 41-9-708, 41-9-710, 41-9-713, and 41-9-714,
36 Code of Alabama 1975, to increase the number of tribes
37 represented on the Alabama Indian Affairs Commission; to
38 recognize additional tribes in the state; to provide further
39 for the powers and duties of the commission; to provide for
40 the salary of the executive director of the commission; to
41 provide requirements for the executive director of the
42 commission; and to make nonsubstantive, technical revisions to
43 update the existing code language to current style.
44 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
45 Section 1. Sections 41-9-708, 41-9-710, 41-9-713, and
46 41-9-714, Code of Alabama 1975, are amended to read as
47 follows:
